<subSubSection id="10D3F6689D09586BA9CB092155F975EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="63212F6C331E2E9D97B01984A6FBEEEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B0184810A39172A4B6A03554E168B4EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
The specific epithet is a noun in apposition and refers to the tartar sauce, &quot;salsa 
<taxonomicName id="A00BD1009607B841341AF7A402A545F2" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa tartara" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tartara">Salsa tartara</taxonomicName>
&quot; in Spanish, one of the favourite salsas of the junior 
<normalizedToken id="AF9A8DED92F57B42626ED5EB51595F31" originalValue="author’s">author's</normalizedToken>
wife.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="30A17545247DD3EBE8274FABA35154D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D1E3A6A491378ABDD090A27F6647163E" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D51FDCA1786B45E5634FDAE4BD45E3EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Like 
<taxonomicName id="43D571FEA21125367E628824447AC542" genus="S." lsidName="S. canalae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="canalae">
<emphasis id="3AD9E31DFE3D3997746AE74668F0D6D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. canalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. males, those of S. 
<taxonomicName id="97795EC49E9C8142705CB2BB80DAF73C" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa tartara" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tartara">
<emphasis id="52E96CC644B525CEDB03AEF9CAB99854" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa tartara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. have two patellar setae on the pedipalp; however, can be separated by the strong curved conductor (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F42ED74A5FD98970226385064CCBE77E" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22C</figureCitation>
) that is absent in 
<taxonomicName id="A9380F930ED883C1AA39CE206BDA37D1" genus="S." lsidName="S. canalae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="canalae">
<emphasis id="3506F4EFBA456CE9C835B026359EE2B6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. canalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. Female epigynes are much longer than wide, similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="AA7C29F91035B7EA03A2A85C3C429EE7" genus="S." lsidName="S. rueda" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="rueda">
<emphasis id="21E1DB5FAED2881FCCFA1BAA0F9B05A2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. rueda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., but they lack the longitudinal central ridge of that species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A4993C29F871E7F5218449E7B6AF1C10" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20C</figureCitation>
vs. Fig. 
<figureCitation id="81EC3635D6BDD185A21B7EA1685D3255" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Salsa tartara sp. nov., female (AM KS. 70661) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686622" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">23C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="532EEEB53330D5BE79AA7A1BCFEA947F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686620" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" start="Figure 21" startId="F21">
<paragraph id="B3D72B49367F345048DAEABBD56F06D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="AF1C1B4CAB8399A1584B18B4F6309152" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Figure 21.</emphasis>
Distribution records of 
<taxonomicName id="CF0D5E43DD69A52CB32A14FFED2BD5DD" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa rueda" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rueda">
<emphasis id="3DAE1C9B137C2C45E244B0B61D4388CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa rueda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="D8384944CCA35CE21C99833DCE59C693" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa tartara" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tartara">
<emphasis id="971BDE2D21389C656CBCFC4100D3F4CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa tartara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B435918C2376A1F0553516DAF7566A16" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="description">
<paragraph id="884739E982B5A22DCC62CE08A9172A77" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E59A2C3749F8EF1F0C5512AF58FC1E6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="3E2DD3F369E4E2B0FA3DE4CC493E240A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Male</emphasis>
(based on holotype, AM KS.70737) Total length 4.0. Carapace 2.1 long, 1.7 wide, brown, slightly paler in cephalic area (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2E27C0F0728A64FDCE90B91C062FBBFB" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.14, ALE 0.13, PME 0.09, PLE 0.09; row of eyes: AME 0.43, PME 0.38, PLE 1.40. Chelicerae orange-brown; with four promarginal teeth (second basal largest) and three retromarginal teeth (basal largest). Legs yellowish brown mottled in grey on joints; femora I and II basally orange-brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="92B6AF093CFA9952303C3467DECD7722" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22A, B</figureCitation>
). Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 2.4 + 1.1 + 1.9 + 1.9 + 0.8 = 8.1, II - 2.0 + 0.9 + 1.6 + 1.7 + 0.7 = 6.9, III - 1.2 + 0.6 + 0.7 + 0.7 + 0.45 = 3.65, IV - 1.6 + 0.7 + 1.2 + 1.2 + 0.6 = 5.3. Labium 0.31 long, 0.45, brown; endites orange-brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B7835DFE8DF3A5CCDB3FD3A793D82D94" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.0 long, 0.8 wide, orange-brown with dusky discolourations (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DCB6ECEC8542A37CFA3DB9A07F8FE6BB" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 2.2 long, 1.9 wide, dorsum with beige background and olive-grey, irregular folium, laterally dark olive-grey with dark streaks (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DCBAA913D49CFAF6F3F89AB8D37FB4CB" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22A</figureCitation>
); venter olive-brown, laterally with thin, irregular white lines (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A647C3E587F22F9FEEB7481F0D1627E6" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + cymbium = total length): 0.4 + 0.15 + 0.15 + 0.6 = 1.3; paracymbium short with pronounced base and slightly curved apically (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="94623086A0926233B4FDABA56CD96792" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22D</figureCitation>
); median apophysis C-shaped, basally pronounced and with an acute and apically curved pointed tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6B55FD2EE3A3A14AF8311DBA0F6B736F" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22C</figureCitation>
); conductor lobe spatulate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E6D1D92803B574D726FCDF8642D58635" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22C</figureCitation>
); terminal apophysis sub-rectangular; conductor strongly sclerotised and curved basally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="52BD1C5ABC83EFED2E922B0CD5AC1875" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22C</figureCitation>
); embolus short and strongly sclerotised.
</paragraph>
<caption id="AF0278C68C2E7138DD42EA4E41A310D3" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" start="Figure 22" startId="F22">
