<paragraph id="CCF268E7190595C611E3C9D5197CCF86" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="BB4BB02438D20EA3336658F14A540E7E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Female</emphasis>
(based on AM KS.70661): Total length 6.5. Carapace 2.5 long, 2.1 wide; colouration and setae largely as in male (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="60789B8DBFA7E8A7C94A249BF0BE36BE" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Salsa tartara sp. nov., female (AM KS. 70661) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686622" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">23A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.16, ALE 0.14, PME 0.11, PLE 0.10; row of eyes: AME 0.47, PME 0.45, PLE 1.92. Chelicerae colour hue as in male, four promarginal teeth (apical and second basal largest) and three retromarginal (basal largest). Legs similar to male but leg I femora basally not orange (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8F930C2D98CEF8D023AFF1E764BF0F13" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Salsa tartara sp. nov., female (AM KS. 70661) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686622" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">23A, B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + tarsus = total length): 0.7 + 0.3 + 0.4 + 0.8 = 2.2. Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 2.4 + 1.1 + 1.9 + 2.0 + 0.8 = 8.2, II - 2.0 + 1.0 + 1.7 + 1.6 + 0.7 = 7.0, III - 1.4 + 0.6 + 0.7 + 0.7 + 0.5 = 3.9, IV - 1.9 + 0.9 + 1.3 + 1.4 + 0.7 = 6.2. Labium 0.18 long, 0.29 wide, brown; endites dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F1484C4F9D299431F2CCCE4E60B6E137" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Salsa tartara sp. nov., female (AM KS. 70661) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686622" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">23B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.2 long, 1.0 wide, dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1E296C6533E533F41266E1B9BB3CAE8C" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Salsa tartara sp. nov., female (AM KS. 70661) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686622" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">23B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 4.0 long, 4.2 wide, sub-triangular with distinct humeral humps, dorsally mottled olive-grey and white, with darker spots anteriorly and postero-laterally; folium pattern indistinct (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BFB7A0D9949BF14FF4B5E48F76BBC8C5" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Salsa tartara sp. nov., female (AM KS. 70661) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686622" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">23A</figureCitation>
); venter as in male (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9FD1670BFA2D17E11602F112E0953308" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Salsa tartara sp. nov., female (AM KS. 70661) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686622" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">23B</figureCitation>
). Epigyne plate longer than wide and composed of two separate sections; borders thin and atrium wide; scape slightly longer than half of epigyne base, sinuous in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0B8E0BDBF4EB9B3AF3A33FAD0D12627A" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Salsa tartara sp. nov., female (AM KS. 70661) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686622" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">23C, D</figureCitation>
); central division almost sub-rectangular, somewhat wider ventrally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D3AD4A8091C15291FA24FDF4B8792F54" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Salsa tartara sp. nov., female (AM KS. 70661) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686622" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">23E</figureCitation>
). Spermathecae enlarged, occupying most of the epigyne area (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="82221E9F3B857BEEBFC5D86D78FD09DF" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Salsa gen. nov. female epigynes, cleared posterior view A S. fuliginata (L. Koch, 1872), comb. nov. (CVIC 173) B S. brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov. (AM KS. 131087) C S. canalae comb. nov. Berland, 1924, comb. nov. (WAM T 75921) D S. recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov. (WAM T 77362) E S. rueda sp. nov. F S. tartara sp. nov. (AM KS. 7061). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686604" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">5F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
